She's the former TV journalist turned Queen of Spain with a wardrobe that gives the Duchess of Cambridge a run for her money.

And today, for her third royal engagement as Queen, Letizia showcased her good taste once again as she joined her husband, King Felipe VI of Spain, to attend an audience with the Social Solidarity Association at El Pardo Palace in Madrid.

Wearing tailored navy trousers and a tweed blue jacket, the newly appointed Queen proved that she can still look stylish at a smart event.

